Sentencas: BaCe0.9-xYxSn0.1O3-sigma (x = 0.05, 0.1, 0.15, 0.2, 0.25, and 0.3) and BaCe0.8Y0.2O3-delta powders were synthesized by a solid-state reaction method.
Titulo: The chemical stability and conductivity of BaCe0.9-xYxSn0.1O3-δ solid proton conductor for SOFC

Sentencas: XRD analysis revealed that the BaCe0.8Y0.2O3-delta powders obviously decomposed into CeO2 and BaCO3 after exposure in 5% H2O + 5% CO2 + 90% N-2 at 500 degrees C for 10 h. However, samples containing Sn remains unchanged in the same conditions, demonstrating a better stability in the presence Of CO2 and H2O.
Titulo: The chemical stability and conductivity of BaCe0.9-xYxSn0.1O3-δ solid proton conductor for SOFC

Sentencas: The conductivity of BaCe0.9-xYxSn0.1O3-delta increased with the increase of Y content (x <= 0.20), and the highest value was observed at x = 0.20 while the conductivity significantly decreases with x = 0.30 and 0.35.
Titulo: The chemical stability and conductivity of BaCe0.9-xYxSn0.1O3-δ solid proton conductor for SOFC

Sentencas: And the BaCe0.7Sn0.1Y0.2O3-sigma, displays 0.01 S/cm at 700 degrees C in humidified hydrogen.
Titulo: The chemical stability and conductivity of BaCe0.9-xYxSn0.1O3-δ solid proton conductor for SOFC

Sentencas: Thin BaCe0.7Sn0.1Y0.2O3-sigma, electrolyte membranes were prepared through suspension spray combined with in situ sintering at 1400 degrees C. With Nd0.7Sr0.3MnO3-sigma, as cathode, solid oxide fuel cells were assembled and tested with humid hydrogen as fuel and static air as oxidant.
Titulo: The chemical stability and conductivity of BaCe0.9-xYxSn0.1O3-δ solid proton conductor for SOFC

Sentencas: The OCV, peak output and interfacial resistance were 1.04V, 220 mW/cm(2) and 0.95 Omega cm(2) at 700 degrees C, respectively.
Titulo: The chemical stability and conductivity of BaCe0.9-xYxSn0.1O3-δ solid proton conductor for SOFC
